---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="How Post-Purchase Experience Platform parcelLab Champions Data Privacy and Security - parcelLab"
  description="parcelLab achieves SOC 2 Type 1, HIPAA, and ePrivacy certifications, demonstrating commitment to the highest data privacy and security standards."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Post-Purchase</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">How Post-Purchase Experience Platform parcelLab Champions Data Privacy and Security</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2022-08-18">August 18, 2022</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>4 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          To deliver personalized, engaging post-checkout experiences, there is one key requirement: data. Without it, it is impossible to provide customers proactive updates or targeted content. But wherever data is concerned, security and privacy must be a priority.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          parcelLab's data engine cleans and harmonizes customer and carrier data, turning logistical updates into personalized messages. To access the data needed to deliver real-time updates to customers across the world, parcelLab has integrated with hundreds of carriers. The organization understands the importance of data security and privacy, for its customers and their customers alike.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Recently completed external certifications demonstrate this commitment. The company is pleased to announce it has become SOC 2 Type 1, HIPAA, and ePrivacy certified.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">SOC 2 Type I</h2>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
          <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            parcelLab acquired SOC 2 Type I compliance in accordance with American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (AICPA) standards for SOC for Service Organizations. To achieve the certification, the business was audited by Prescient Assurance, a leader in security and compliance attestation for B2B SaaS companies worldwide.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
            The SOC 2 Type I audit report demonstrates to current and future customers that parcelLab will manage their data with the highest standard of security and compliance. The company has already embarked on the next step to become SOC 2 Type II certified and fully enterprise compliant.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">HIPAA</h2>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
          <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            The HIPAA laws are a series of federal regulatory standards that outline the lawful use and disclosure of protected information in the United States. To achieve HIPAA certification, the business successfully demonstrated compliance to the rules laid out by the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) as enforced by the Office for Civil Rights (OCR).
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Achieving this certification underlines the organization's commitment to upholding the highest security and data protection standards in both the healthcare and retail industries.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">ePrivacy</h2>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
          <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            The ePrivacy certification is designed for businesses to demonstrate their commitment to upholding data processing procedures in compliance with GDPR. parcelLab's ePrivacy certification serves as a "seal of approval" that the organization's data management conforms to the requirements of EU law.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Achieving this standard provides third-party industry validation that parcelLab GmbH provides enterprise-level security for customer data secured in its system.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          These certifications reflect parcelLab's ongoing commitment to maintaining the highest standards for data handling, management, and storage -- ensuring that brands and their customers can trust the platform with their most sensitive information.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
